        memory: 'Her family came from Mogadishu by way of three other cities that never fit. Kalamazoo fit — strangely, stubbornly. After the February shootings in 2016, the town turned its grief into structures: a free clinic shift, a community fridge, her entire career. Grief is just love with nowhere to go, so we gave it somewhere.',
